article.headline: Quinnipiac 58, Army 54
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Bryan Geffen had 16 points to lead Quinnipiac in a 58-54 win over Army Sunday. It was a nail-biter with the score tied six times and seven lead changes. The teams were tied at 54-all with about a minute-and-a-half left to play. Jarell Brown fouled Karl Anderson and Evann Baker within seconds of each other. They scored two free throws apiece to seal the win. DeMario Anderson had 12 points for Quinnipiac (4-4), which finished with a 42 percent shooting average. Karl Anderson contributed 9 rebounds and 8 points. The Bobcats led 28-21 at the half. Brown scored 22 for Army (4-5). The Black Knights shot at 39.6 percent. Quinnipiac outrebounded Army 36-29.
